column18: Transcribe the written answer of each participant's guess  of the study's goal.
When you cannot smile, this effects the amusement of funny images
To what extent people follow instructions that are against the inclination not to put a pen in your mouth
Whether holding a pen in your mouth has an influence on your mood en the judgment of cartoons. Because you cannot smile with a pen in you mouth
Ability to concentrate with physical performance
Whether holding a pen in your mouth distracts you from performing tasks?
Finding a way for tasks to be done by another body part. A method needs to be developed to teach people how to do this. This can be acheived with the results of the study.
I think the pen in the mouth is meant as a distraction en that it is about understanding media messages when you are doing something else at the same time (multitasking)
The influence of motoric changes (e.g., not having hands) on thinking processes
The study whether people can do two things at once while performing a hard task
To study whether it is possible for people with a handicap to perform normal task that they for instance have to do at school
No idea
To see whether people become more or less amused with a hard task
To study how people experience the use of a body part for motoric performance that they are not used to
To what extent a physical task that you don't perform often in daily life influences the understanding of information
It's an experiment to study whether the difficulty of making a judgment has an influence on the judgment
Th extent to which someone follows instructions with only a camera present, when that activity is difficult to perform
Test to what extent the mouth can be an alternative for the use of the hands in people with a handicap
To see whether it is possible to perform tasks like this with other body parts than the hands. For people who cannot use their hands
Concentration and understanding when you have a pen in the mouth
Kijken naar how coordination is with different tasks that you need to perform in a usual way
Study whether a handicap influences your sense of humor and your experience of humor
to analyse psychomotoric abilities
Combining knowledge with an unusual task and subsequently feeling with an unusual task. This way both brain hemispheres are tsted during a unusual task
Testing whether your ability to think is altered when you are doing a difficult or unusual task
To find an alternative way to communicate without arms or legs
Find out to what extent holding a pen with your mouth influences thinking and normal ? To what extent it distracts from simpel things
In what way and how well people without a handycap can peform a task like this (with a different body part)
If holding a pen in your mouth makes you smile more about cartoons/find those cartoons funnier
To study how people adapt when they have a handicap
If you have to fill something in in a different way, with a pen in your mouth instead of by hand, is that imfluencing concentration and thinking abilities?
no idea
test motoric skills in combination with laughing. What is the influence of the level of humor on someone's motoric movements
To see how long people can hold a pen in their mouth without it moving
See whether there is a connection between ability to concentrate and doing things with other body parts than are usual for certain tasks
To see whether people can hold their attention/concebtration when they have to focus on something else at the same tim (holding the pen in the mouth and writing neatly)

The goal is probably to see how well people can concentrate if they are being distracted because they focus on how they have to perform something, in this case the distraction is the pen in the mouth. If I would not have a pen in my mouth I could probably concentrate better on the cartoons
distraction from what the research is really about
See to what extent being amused/distracted influences your performance or concentration ability
How hard is het to focus when you have to do something in a compleletly different way (pen in your mouth) en focus on how hard it is to do that
See how well people are able to fill in thing without their hands
To see whether people find it difficult to perform easy task in another way
To see whether people can perform simple task not in the "normal" way, but have to focus on something else
Measure the feelings of people towards people with a handicap by letting participants experience not being able to write with their hand and measuring difficulty and their sense of humor.
To measure how a pen between your affects your mood and also to be impaired of something that you take for granted daly. It affects how quickly irritated (?) you get
See what the link is between learning motor skills and emotie
Hoe easy you take something from others and how easy you are influenced to do something
For how much many can I let people with a pen in their mouth make a fool of themselves on video
To examine whether a complicated task influences whether you like something and whether you attend to something, like the cartoons
Effect of humor amusement on being able to hold a pen in your mouth? Effect on your musles and concentration ability
This research is very good because it gives us information on how and wat someone with a handicap
effect of emotion on your coordination
Using a pen in the mouth to see how people do this who have never done this before
To develop an understanding of human motor skills in cases where full motor control is lacking. Observing the way people struggle will help them eventually aid tehm in using easier-to-uuse techniques
To see whether people can do daily things like laughing with a pen in their mouth
To see whether there is a way for people without hands to let them write with their mouth. They see whether this is possible with this research
To waht extent can we perform a task with a pen in our mouth which of course creates saliva while we are getting amused because of what we see which generates even more saliva
How do you judge jokes about handicaps or other people's limitations after you yourself experienced a limitation
To guide body part that you use for other things normally. How strong is the mind over the body
How good is your psychomotoric coordination
testing coordination
To see whether everyday objects like a pen are a useful alterative for expeensive protheses to help people with a handicap express themselves
How people deal with alterantiev organs when an essential one has dropped away. Help to train people to use other organs for writing if that cannot be done with the hand
To see whether people can perform tasks without using the usual body part. To what extent do people understand a task when the performance of that task is harder?
If coordination with teh mouth becomes better or worse when you see humoristic imagery, with a change in concentration as a resul
no idea

I think this experiment gives the participant a new choice changing in attitude while focussing on a "mentally loaded"task like this experiment. While writing this down I put pen in my mouth per instruction
What is the relationship between psychomotoric ability and sense of humor?
To see whether taking on a certain facial expression holding certain muscles has an influence on how you judge things
no idea
To research if an unusual performance influences how you understand cartoons and other tasks
See whether you find cartoons funnier when you have a smiling expression on your face
If people without using their teeth, but only with lip-eye coordination have control in certain tasks
See whether you make different choices when you have a pen in the mouth
To show people without a handicap what it is like to live with a handicap
See which side writing is hardest for physically handicapped people and if you read quicker with saliva coming
To see to what extent people follow instructions
I think the goal is to study whether my concentration and understanding of certain things (cartoons) is decreased because the pen in my mouth also requires concentration
Body language with a frustrating task
To study whether you can write with your mouth for a longer period without salivating
Hoe hard is it to write without hands. Influence of creativity/humor?
Something with physicalcoordination and the influence on the brain
The more text a cartoon has, the more you need to read, the less amused you are because you have to hold the pen in your mouth longer, which isn't easy
The goal is to find out if the mouth can be used as a solution for the motoric disruption in paralyzed people
To see whether people find things more funny if they have to do funny things, such as writing with a pen in your mouth

I think the goal is to see whether cheap alternatuves kan work for people with a physical disability. With the cartoons was studies if you still have enough focus using this alternative to think about other things such as humor
Whether you can attend to other things such as cartoons when your focus is on the pen.
How do people deal with a sudden handicap? How quicly does the body adapt to a new situation
Measure the extent to which people find cartoons funny

To see whether people with pen in their mouth find the cartoons just as funny as people without a pen in their mouth. I think that you would find them less funny with pen, because you cannot move your facial muscles freely.
The extent to which your sense of humor is influences when you have to conectrate on a new task
To generate knowledge about the ability of people to perform tasks with a pen when they can only use their mouth
The goal is to see how well lips can serve the function to express yourself when you cannot do this in another way
To see whether people are concentrated with joy and understanding and less clumsy as a result

To see to what extent handicapped people can use a pen with their mouth if they cannot use their hands. Also to see whether a pen in the mouth can influence the level of concentration (i.e., understand and concentrate on the cartoons). Multitasking!
To study how well you can coordinate the movement of a pen with your mouth/teeth/movement of the head.
Study how people react to abnormal tasks?
To see what happens when you use body parts for a task hat you normally perform with another body part. Does this influence perception?

The goal is to see how easy or hard it is to perform a task in an unusual way (i.e., writing with the mouth instead of the hand). That becomes more difficult when you find something funny (the cartoons), because then you can keep a pen in your mouth less easily
I think the goal of this research has to do with how positive feelings (evoked by the cartoons) influence the writing ability of handicapped people
Develop technology for people with a handicap that makes thier life more easy
Test how people with phsical/motoric disabilities perform tasks with body arts that are normally not used for this.
research what the influence is of this way of communicating (with the pen in the mouth) on appreciation/emotion/understanding of the cartoons
I think the goal is to exaine whether this method is suitable for people with a physical disability to write in this way without losing focus or understanding of the task
Whether you comply with the task, and not cheat and keep the pen in your mouth
To see whether you respond differently to the cartoons when you have to answer in an unusual way, perform an action that feels strange
Measure psychomotoric abilities
Research whether your facial expression (when you have a pen in yoru mouth) influences your mood (being amused by the cartoons or not)

To create insight into out of the ordinary motoric abilities. The practical relevance is that you know what you can do when you suddenly become handicapped, you can offer solutions that probably work. This is uncomfortable to research which actual handicapped people because they already have many worries
The goal is to see how hard it is for eople with disabilities to perform ceratin daily routines and how they expreience that

The goal is to see whether certain facial expressions/muscles influence how funny/amusing you find something. Holding a pen in the mouth creates a certain facial expression, or you smile because you are happy, or aare you happy becaus eyou smile?
Whether using unknown motoric abilities has an influence on emotions and emotional experience
To study how well people can use body parts for things that thos ebody parts are not made for
The development of simpler cheaper ways that could help people with a physical disability to perform daily tasks
Research solutions for physical abilities (like having no hands for writing)
Do we understand things better or more amusing when we have to perform certain tasks in another way then we are used to
To see how well a person without a handicap and without training can perform the previous tasks
Being distracted and judging cartoons?
It probably has something to do with the pen in your mouth and only the cartoons. So see how people experience the cartoons when they focus on something else as well

To observe and research to what extent you can note things in a different way (with a pen in your mouth) if you cannot do it the usual way. And if you still find things amusing wven though it is harder to do . Whether you can still enjoy things
To see whether holding a pen in your mouth influences how funny you find things
How good are your motoric skills and do you find things funny more quickly
coordination and motoric skills
Goal: to see how people write with a pen in their mouth and examine how well they can learn this. To develop a cheap way to help people who cannot write with their hands
because it is uncomfortable to hold the pen it is maybe harder to process information. This is what you study
The goal was to develop a better method and cheaper technology for people who cannot write with their hands?

The goal is to study how people perform tasks with parts of their body that they would normally never use for those tasks. With this new aids can be deveoped that people with a handicap can use in theior daily life
To see how well participants hold the position
by holding the pen in your mouth you create a sort of smile, with as a result that you will find the pictures more funny then when you do not have a pen in yoru mouth
To see how well a person can perform actions with a body part that is not meant to do that. It is examine  whether particular distraction play a role
concentration and humor?
test motoric skills with emotion/amusement
with an unpleasant physical action  looking at the funniness of the cartoons and whether that influenced each other
See whether people can still focus when they perform a common action in an unusual way
To sudy to what extent a hard unnatural task has an influence on whether you get or do not get or like or do not like cartoons
How well people are capable to perform common acts in a different way and how emotions influences this performance
To see how quickly people learn a "trick" and how long they can hold a pen without being uncomfortable (i.e., saliva). This way we can see whether the pen is a ? (I don't think so)
To study how well people are able to guide the pen with their mouth and whether this changes when they find something funny
Behavior of people who are confronted for the first time with a disability with people who have been living with a disability
To test physical coordination
To see whether the same actions can be performed with a different body part and whether this has an effect on the results

Mayby dependent upon the type of task, whether you hold the pen differently in your mouth, and vice versa whether a different way of writing with your mouth makes you find different things funny or funnier

The goal is whether holding the pen in bwteen your lips and writing like this has an influence on how funny you find something (the cartoons). Most importantly, whether using different brain regions than normally influences how you expreiences sensations
How well you can hold a pen in your mouth while you are laughing
Judgng certain things when you are concentrated on one thing and when you are cincentrated on multiple things (holding the pen straight)
